The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                               Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) has opened its third delivery centre in Mexico. The company will hire 500 professionals for the centre and offer advanced IT, consultancy, BPO, industrial and engineering services from this facility.                            
	 Balmer Lawries turnover for the year ended March 31, 2009,has increased 13 per cent to Rs 1,776 crore from Rs 1,571 crore a year ago. Net profit has grown 17 per cent to Rs 102 crore.                             
	 Ramsarup Industries has started production from a 500 TPD DRI plant in Bengal and waste heat recovery boiler at Kharagpur. The plant will generate Rs 4 crore in revenues per month.                             
	 Audi has announced the introduction of three engines for the A4  the 3.0 TDI quattro, the 2.0 TFSI and the 1.8 TFSI.                             
	 Vodafone Essar has launched three bonus cards for its prepaid customers in Calcutta. The cards are priced at Rs 33, Rs 57 and Rs 123 with a validity of one month, two months and six months, respectively.                                                                                                                     ADVERTISEMENT                   
